reason.tex:
%text
The distance between the points $(1,0,0)$ and $(0,1,1)$ is
%
\begin{align}
  d &= \sqrt{(x_2-x_1)^2+(y_2-y_1)^2+(z_2-z_1)^2} \\
    &=\sqrt{(0-1)^2+(1-0)^2+(1-0)^2}=\sqrt{3}
\end{align} \\
%text
If the direction ratios $a$, $b$ and $c$ are $-1$, $1$ and $1$ respectively, the direction cosines $l$, $m$ and $n$ are,
%
\begin{align}
  l  &=\dfrac{a}{d}=\dfrac{-1}{\sqrt{3}} \\
  m&=\dfrac{b}{d}=\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{3}} \\
  n &= \dfrac{c}{d}=\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{3}}
\end{align}
